## Goal
Fix web UI hanging on load (sidebar never renders, stuck on "loading").

## Root Cause
The dashboard page (`/`) makes **11 API calls** on load. Three endpoints had no server-side timeouts and could hang indefinitely:

| Endpoint | Problem | Fix |
|----------|---------|-----|
| `GET /api/plugins` | `plugin.health_check()` called **sequentially** on ALL plugins with no timeout → 1 slow plugin hangs the whole endpoint | Added `asyncio.wait_for(plugin.health_check(), timeout=3.0)` |
| `GET /api/diagnostics` | 5 sequential health checks (models, integrations, voice, features, environment) with **no timeouts** → any one hanging blocks all | Added `asyncio.wait_for()` with 3-5s timeout per check |
| `GET /api/diagnostics/models` | `health_check_all()` had no timeout → Ollama ping could hang | Added `asyncio.wait_for(..., timeout=5.0)` |
| `GET /api/diagnostics/integrations` | Same pattern | Added `asyncio.wait_for(..., timeout=5.0)` |
| `TerminalPanel` `api.diagnostics.all()` | Client-side had **no abort signal** | Added 5s AbortController timeout |
| `StatusBar` | 5 sequential calls blocked each other; no abort on 4/5 | Changed to parallel `Promise.allSettled` with per-call `Promise.race` timeouts |
| `api.diagnostics.all()` in api.ts | Didn't accept `AbortSignal` | Added optional `signal` parameter |

## Changed Files
- `core/routes/operations.py:118-131` — plugin health_check timeout
- `core/routes/diagnostics.py:19-105` — all 5 diagnostic checks wrapped in `asyncio.wait_for`
- `core/routes/diagnostics.py:107-134` — models/integrations endpoints with timeout
- `web/src/app/page.tsx:223-231` — TerminalPanel 5s abort on diagnostics.all()
- `web/src/components/layout/StatusBar.tsx:28-70` — parallel with per-call timeouts
- `web/src/lib/api.ts:358` — diagnostics.all() accepts AbortSignal

